The paper deals with the problem of creating an intelligent recommender system that can determine the intent of the user in each session and provide better recommendations. This involves encoding user activity, reducing high-dimensional data using tensor factorization techniques, and combining user activity data with contextual information. The paper also discusses the provision for feedback to update the model weights. Based on these aspects, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
